T h e method is presently being applied to the problem of wave number selection and finite amplitude stability in a convective layer (the Benard problem, see e.g. [5]) and to a numerical study of energy cascading between large and small eddies in a model of turbulence (the Green-Taylor problem [ó]). The results of these studies and further details on the numerical method will be presented in a forthcoming paper and will point out crucial differences between the behavior of solutions of the Navier-Stokes equations in two and three space dimensions.

